cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.AR, cs.PL 

This paper deals with the implementation of rank and select operations in succinct data structures, which are primarily used in data structures and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the impact of the new implementation on CPU instruction cache performance and memory-access parallelism, which falls under the category of cs.AR (Architecture). The paper also involves the study of the performance of bit-vector-select, which is related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper involves the implementation of machine-word select using x86 instructions, which falls under the category of cs.PL (Programming Languages).
